jm00july5ucb

This README describes the function of most of the routines in
/deep1/ioannis/trgb/idl, which were written to analyze Keck/HST
TRGB data.  The routines are described alphabetically, with 
the most important ones marked with asterixes.


BOOT_RESPONSE: Bootstrap resample a stellar luminosity function.

MULTIPHOT_SCRIPT: Generate a script that runs all pre-MULTIPHOT and
		  MULTIPHOT routines.

MULTIPHOT_SCRIPT_WRAPPER: Wrap MULTIPHOT_SCRIPT on a galaxy list.

PLOT_LFUNCTION: Plot a stellar luminosity function.

PLOT_RESPONSE: Plot the Sobol response filter.

READ_MULTIPHOT: Read a MULTIPHOT output photometry file and generate an 
		objname_starlist.dat photometry file.

TRGB_DACOSTA: Return an array of structures which holds the I-band 
	      magnitudes and the colors of the RGB's of the globular
	      clusters described in Dacosta & Armandroff 1990.
		
TRGB_DATAPATH: Return the full datapath to the data.

TRGB_EDGE: Detect the TRGB from the stellar luminosity function
	   with the Sobol filter using bootstrap resampling.

TRGB_HST_REDUX: Creates symbolic links to the data files, applies
		the data-quality mask, flags cosmic rays, creates
		a mean, cosmic-ray rejected image from which a 
		starlist can be generated, creates a sub-directory
		structure, and writes out the first data files by
		chip number into appropriate subdirectories.

TRGB_HST_REDUX_WRAPPER: Run TRGB_HST_REDUX on a galaxy list.

TRGB_HST_THRESHOLD: Generate a plot of threshold versus number of stars
		    found.

TRGB_LFUNCTION: Generate and plot a luminosity function.

TRGB_OBJECT_DATA: General informational structure on each TRGB object.

TRGB_PRINTOSCREEN: Print some basic results to the screen given a TRGB
		   edge detection.

TRGB_READATA: Read the TRGB photometry data.

TRGB_REGIONS: Interactively allow the user to select out certain stars
	      based on their positions on the sky (relative to the whole
	      galaxy) to better isolate the old, metal-poor stellar
	      population.  Generates objname_starlist_halo.dat and
	      objname_starlist_core.dat photometry files.

TRGB_ROBUST: Robustly average magnitudes.

WFPC2_CRREJ: Flag and reject cosmic rays and the bad pixels in the 
	     data-quality mask in the raw WFPC2 data.

WFPC2_LINKS: Create symbolic links to raw WFPC2 data.

WFPC2_DITHERING: Calculate the amount of dithering between WFPC2 images
		 using the astrometry information in the headers and by
		 matching starlists.

Z_DISTANCE: Generate a plot of Peebles' redshift-distance relation 
	    (Figure 1, 1988, Apj, 332, 17).


ALLFRAME ROUTINES:
------------------

DAOHEADER: Create a two-line DAOPHOT header.

READ_DAOPHOT: Read a DAOPHOT photometry (.ap) file into a data array.

TRGB_ALLFRAME: Master ALLFRAME program

TRGB_APCORRECT: Determine the aperture corrections for the Keck data (UNFINISHED).

TRGB_CALIBRATE: Calibrate (aperture, exposure time and airmass corrections)
		Keck photometry to a standard system and create and
		objname_IVmags.dat photometry file.	

TRGB_CHECKCHI: Check the stellar distribution of ALLFRAME CHI values.

TRGB_DAOMASTER: Create a .raw ALLFRAME photometry file.

TRGB_FIXPSF: Convert an IRAF psf to a DAOPHOT psf.

TRGB_HST_CALIBRATE: Calibrate HST/WFPC2 ALLFRAME photometry onto a 
		    standard system.

TRGB_HST_MASTER: Master HST/WFPC2 ALLFRAME program.

TRGB_MAKEALS: Create the two-line header .als files needed by ALLFRAME.

TRGB_MAKEMCH: Create a DAOPHOT transformation (.mch) file.

TRGB_MAKEMINI: Interactively select a miniature photometric starlist.

TRGB_MAKEOPT: Generate DAOPHOT .opt parameter files.

TRGB_MASTER: Master ALLFRAME photometry analysis of the Keck TRGB data.

TRGB_PRE_ALLFRAME: Iteratively run ALLFRAME on a smaller starlist to determine 
		   the PROFILE and PERCENT ERROR that will give the best CHI 
		   distribution.

TRGB_HST_PRE_STARLIST: 

TRGB_STARLIST: Generate a master ALLFRAME starlist (.mag) using
	       ALLSTAR iteratively.


